<p><b>  Report of the Special Rapporteur on contemporary forms of 
slavery, including its causes and consequences,  
Gulnara Shahinian 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Addendum 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Follow-up mission to Mauritania</b>&#8727; **<b> 
</b></p>
<p><i>Summary 
</i> The Special Rapporteur on contemporary forms of slavery, including its causes and 
consequences, conducted a follow-up mission to Mauritania from 24 to 27 February 2014. 
The main objective of her visit was to assess new developments since her first mission in 
2009 and the initiatives taken by the Government in response to her recommendations. In 
particular, she assessed the status of the road map for the implementation of her 
recommendations to end slavery in Mauritania, which had been prepared in cooperation 
with the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights, and to 
promote its formal adoption. The Special Rapporteur also assessed existing legislation, 
institutional mechanisms, programmes and policies aimed at combating all forms of 
slavery, as well as their application in practice. 
</p>
<p> The Special Rapporteur hails the commitment and cooperation of Mauritania. She 
found that the Government had made good progress in taking legislative and institutional 
measures aimed at fighting forms of slavery in Mauritania. Following her visit, on 6 March 
2014, the Government formally adopted the road map, which marks a new stage in the 
Government&#8217;s fight against all forms of slavery and slavery-like practices, moving from 
adherence to implementation of her recommendations. In particular, the road map provides 
</p>
<p>                                                          
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>&#8727;
 The summary of the present report is circulated in all official languages. The report, which is annexed 
</p>
<p>to the summary, is circulated in the language of submission and in French only. 
 
</p>
<p>**
 Late submission. 
</p>
